Job Description

Meet the Team

Join a dynamic, collaborative engineering team dedicated to building scalable, high-impact web applications that empower our customers. We leverage the latest technologies and best practices, fostering an environment where innovation, learning, and teamwork drive our success.

-------------------------

Your Impact

As a Full-Stack Developer, you will be an integral part of our team, developing both frontend and backend components of robust web applications. Youâ€™ll contribute to designing engaging user experiences, building scalable backend services, and ensuring our deployments are fast and reliable. Your work will directly help shape the future of our digital solutions and make a tangible impact for our users.

* Develop, test, and maintain web applications with both frontend and backend components.
* Design responsive, user-friendly interfaces using modern frontend frameworks such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.
* Build scalable and maintainable backend services and APIs using frameworks such as Django, Flask, Node.js, or similar.
* Collaborate on database design, management, and optimization for SQL and/or NoSQL databases.
* Implement and maintain CI/CD pipelines using tools like Jenkins, GitHub Actions, or similar, ensuring fast and reliable deployments.
* Manage code repositories on GitHub, contributing to branch strategy, pull requests, and code reviews.
* Write automation scripts in Python or other scripting languages to improve workflows, testing, and monitoring.
* Debug, troubleshoot, and optimize application performance across the stack.
* Stay up-to-date with emerging technologies and help drive best practices within the team.

-------------------------

Minimum Qualifications

* Proven experience as a Full-Stack Developer or in a similar role, with a strong portfolio of web applications.
* Proficiency in frontend technologies: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and at least one modern frontend framework (e.g., React, Angular, Vue).
* Strong backend development skills with Python (or Node.js, Java, Ruby) and experience building RESTful APIs or GraphQL.
* Familiarity with databases (e.g., PostgreSQL, MySQL, MongoDB) and basic data modeling.
* Hands-on experience with GitHub and CI/CD tools like Jenkins, GitHub Actions, or similar.

-------------------------

Preferred Qualifications

* Understanding of web architecture, performance, and security best practices.
* Basic knowledge of cloud services (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP) and container technologies (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).
* Excellent problem-solving, communication, and collaboration skills.
* A strong desire to learn, contribute, and grow in a dynamic engineering environment.
* Experience with automation scripting to streamline workflows, testing, or monitoring.